There's this girl that I have to take taxis together with often for work and when we get off at our destination I always open the car door for her, but she has the habit of slamming it shut every time so I have to pull my fingers back in the last second before they get amputated.

I like it. Keeps me sharp. Some might say I should not place my fingers where a car door can crush them. I say nothing matters if your reflexes are firing quickly. It's like that video of a man punching a bear trap and retracting his hand in the millisecond before it snaps. Boom.
Ideally there should be 7-8 different women trying to kill you or cause you bodily harm every day. Most of them professionals.

The fact that work friendships are not "real" and generally even if you think you're friends with your coworkers once you quit you'll forget each other in a few months and never hang out again is true, but the friendship between kebab shop owner and a client (me) remains eternal.

Once you know my order comes with double onion and hot peppers without me mentioning it I am ready to die for you. We can meet decades after the kebab store has closed down due to hygiene violations but I will still honor our bond.

The Hebrew word for soul ("nephesh") also being used in Semitic languages to mean "appetite" sort of proves my idea that the soul in religion and the metabolism in biology are very overlapping concepts... To be alive means to have an appetite...

Apparently it also is used for "desires", which obviously relates to the appetite, but the concept is a bit corrupted in the West right now so I'm thinking of it more in the Dr. Pyotr Anokhin "acceptor of action" idea of the brain always envisioning and predicting potentialities.
